span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/30/02 7:40:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> FYI:<br>
<br>
If you engage Ragefire with a Warrior and Cleric only... That is NOT sufficient force for Ragefire. A GM will say the spawn is NOT YOURS unless you have sufficient force. This stops someone for kiting a mob around for hours in hopes of getting people there.<br>
<br>
If a Raid is there with sufficient force, then the GM will default that raid with the spawn.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uconnavardosg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ConnavarDOSG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/30/02 8:08:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> The coming month will be a real, test of tests for this server.<br>
<br>
Can the folks who constantly quote The Rules (TM) as an escape mechanism to evade common courtesy win?<br>
<br>
Or will the clerics currently camping Rage as part of an informal list succeed in their efforts?<br>
<br>
We've already thrown in our support for Syllie, but rest assured if Rage is up and ANY campers need help with taking him out, please don't hestitate to call upon DoSG.<br>
<br>
Just because Verant makes the rules as they are, what counts is how we as players interpret them.<br>
<br>
Cheers<br>
<br>
Conn<br>
