SRC="http://website.lineone.net/~mattgbaker/Handbag.jpg"></CENTER><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ugemlin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gemlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/30/02 11:23:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> Just saying you better live by what the GMs set forth, because theres over 4000+ people on quellious. <br>
<br>
Now lets look at human nature.<br>
<br>
80% of them will help you out, and respect people who's been camping something for hours or days at end. And these people will respect a cleric who's been camping ragefire for days.<br>
<br>
20% of them wont.<br>
<br>
Those 20 percent of the people will take advantage of situations, KS, steal, cheat etc. I consistently see MOTD's about GMs warning people against others. (Like trades for example). <br>
<br>
Because of those 20 percent of the people out there, you have to strictly play by the rules so that a GM will take your side in a issue. <br>
<br>
